    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Nievergelt &amp; Hinrichs &middot; Ch. 8 &middot; <a href="https://textbookequity.org/algorithms-and-data-structures/">Algorithms and Data Structures</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><strong>Convex hull</strong> wraps a point set in the smallest convex polygon. Graham scan does it in O(n log n). <strong>Line intersection</strong>, <strong>closest pair</strong>, and <strong>Voronoi diagrams</strong> extend these ideas to richer geometric problems.</p>
    </div>

