    <h3>Cross product orientation test</h3>
    <p>The foundation of computational geometry. Given three points P, Q, R: the cross product (Q-P) x (R-P) tells you whether R is left of, right of, or on the line PQ. Positive = left turn, negative = right turn, zero = collinear.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Cross product: orientation test
; (Q-P) x (R-P) > 0 means left turn (counterclockwise)

(define (cross px py qx qy rx ry)
  (- (* (- qx px) (- ry py))
     (* (- qy py) (- rx px))))

; Three points: P=(0,0), Q=(1,0), R=(0,1)
(display "P(0,0) Q(1,0) R(0,1): ")
(display (cross 0 0 1 0 0 1)) (newline)  ; positive = left turn

(display "P(0,0) Q(1,0) R(0,-1): ")
(display (cross 0 0 1 0 0 -1)) (newline)  ; negative = right turn

(display "P(0,0) Q(1,0) R(2,0): ")
(display (cross 0 0 1 0 2 0))  ; zero = collinear
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Cross product orientation test
def cross(p, q, r):
    return (q[0]-p[0]) * (r[1]-p[1]) - (q[1]-p[1]) * (r[0]-p[0])

print(f"Left turn:  {cross((0,0), (1,0), (0,1))}")   # positive
print(f"Right turn: {cross((0,0), (1,0), (0,-1))}")   # negative
print(f"Collinear:  {cross((0,0), (1,0), (2,0))}")    # zero
`} />
    </div>

    <h3>Graham scan</h3>
    <p>Sort points by polar angle around the lowest point. Walk through the sorted points, keeping only left turns. O(n log n) for the sort, O(n) for the scan.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Graham scan: convex hull in O(n log n)
; Simplified version using sorted-by-x approach

(define points
  (list (list 0 0) (list 1 3) (list 2 1) (list 3 4)
        (list 4 2) (list 5 0) (list 2 2) (list 3 1)))

(define (cross-val p q r)
  (- (* (- (car q) (car p)) (- (cadr r) (cadr p)))
     (* (- (cadr q) (cadr p)) (- (car r) (car p)))))

; Sort by x, then y
(define sorted
  (sort points (lambda (a b)
    (or (< (car a) (car b))
        (and (= (car a) (car b)) (< (cadr a) (cadr b)))))))

; Build upper and lower hulls
(define (build-half pts)
  (fold-left
    (lambda (hull p)
      (let loop ((h hull))
        (if (and (>= (length h) 2)
                 (<= (cross-val (list-ref h (- (length h) 2))
                                (list-ref h (- (length h) 1))
                                p) 0))
            (loop (reverse (cdr (reverse h))))
            (append h (list p)))))
    (list) pts))

(define upper (build-half sorted))
(define lower (build-half (reverse sorted)))

(define hull (append (reverse (cdr (reverse upper)))
                     (reverse (cdr (reverse lower)))))

(display "Hull: ") (display hull)
`} />

